<TITLE> Vieri to try his hand at poker </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MILAN, April 17 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Former Italy striker Christian Vieri has decided to compete in poker competitions but has no plans to hang up his boots just yet. The 35-year-old former Inter Milan forward is without a club having quit Serie A side Atalanta this month after fans jeered him during a training session. "I enjoy cards a lotbut my future is still in football. I will stop when I'm fed up chasing after a ball and I am not bored yet. When I'm retired, who knows, I could become a professional poker player," he told Sportweek magazine
